{"paperId": "1a88e53ab07328a497b8e153e18c78cb174e0e89", "abstract": "This paper introduces a novel orchestration framework, called CFO (Computation Flow Orchestrator), for building, experimenting with, and deploying interactive NLP (Natural Language Processing) and IR (Information Retrieval) systems to production environments. We then demonstrate a question answering system built using this framework which incorporates state-of-the-art BERT based MRC (Machine Reading Com- prehension) with IR components to enable end-to-end answer retrieval. Results from the demo system are shown to be high quality in both academic and industry domain specific settings. Finally, we discuss best practices when (pre-)training BERT based MRC models for production systems. Screencast links: - Short video (< 3 min): http: //ibm.biz/gaama_demo - Supplementary long video (< 13 min): http://ibm.biz/gaama_cfo_demo", "venue": "Conference on Empirical Methods in Natural Language Processing", "year": 2019, "citationCount": 9, "influentialCitationCount": 1, "openAccessPdf": {"url": "https://www.aclweb.org/anthology/D19-3006.pdf", "status": "HYBRID"}, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": "A question answering system built using a novel orchestration framework which incorporates state-of-the-art BERT based MRC (Machine Reading Com- prehension) with IR components to enable end-to-end answer retrieval."}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [0.3183537721633911, 0.17854030430316925, -0.2404860258102417, -0.16058988869190216, -0.6684504151344299, -0.5387377738952637, 0.6792389154434204, 0.0495472252368927, -0.11236152052879333, -0.028190121054649353, 0.7593699097633362, -0.4911780059337616, -0.10353689640760422, 0.07518892735242844, -0.18966704607009888, 0.320977121591568, -0.6955839991569519, 0.9043140411376953, -0.7603592276573181, -0.3830536901950836, -0.05036645382642746, -0.28962743282318115, -1.2970322370529175, 0.6936919689178467, 0.5912785530090332, 0.5367720127105713, -0.0983364